?gid=stephencrowley>Stephen Crowley</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/18/03 5:22:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rules Clarification - Obfuscate</span><hr size=1> Two questions I wanted to ask - both to staff and veteran players - regarding the use of Obfuscate.<br>
<br>
1) What kind of justification, if any, does a player with Auspex need to use that Discipline to spot someone in &quot;Ob&quot;? The book uses the term &quot;An individual with Auspex (or another power of supernatural sensitivity) may penetrate Obfuscate if he is already looking for hidden individuals.&quot; Obviously, this is a little vague in terms of putting it into practice. If a OOC a player knows there's nobody around in ob, they won't bother using it. If they know there is somebody around OOC, they certainly will. Is this something that's come up in discussion before?<br>
<br>
2) And this is somewhat related to what Yoshi brought up. Regarding video cameras and digital cameras and other film, does an individual in obfuscate appear, say, if we're talking about a tape-delay security camera? The book is very fuzzy on such subjects.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stephencrowley>Stephen Crowley</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 2/18/03 9:42:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hart@scbnforum58570>Hart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/18/03 5:31:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Clarication - Obfuscate</span><hr size=1> 1)  As the book example, if a character has reason to &quot;search&quot; a space with auspex, for instance to &quot;secure&quot; a space, or if they have been given reason to believe someone may be there, then using auspex to try to weed out sneaks and such.  Also it is generally played out that if someone does something suspicious in obfuscate that might give them away, such as knocking into something, that someone with auspex or hightened senses might find them out.  However players should be given the benefit of the doubt, a 175# player in dumb but pretty shoes stomping along may indeed be playing a delicate waif, traipsing gracefully along.<br>
<br>
2)  Obfuscate is not proof against video at basic and intermediate levels, I do believe there are some advanced disciplines that can beat the security... but my book is not at hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theherald@scbnforum58570>The Herald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Clan Malkavian</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/18/03 11:29:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Clarication - Obfuscate</span><hr size=1> One other thing to keep in mind for role playing purposes is that Obfuscate is a MENTAL, not a PHYSICAL discipline.  This means that if I am successful in my challenge I am fooling your perception of your senses, not the senses themselves.  Therefore you show up on cameras because you /are/ there, even if no one can see you. <br>
<br>
In addition, it is usually considered by myself and others 'foul play' to immdiately look for obfuscated people when they come into snooping range.  Even if your character is paranoid, walking around with heightened senses on is a great way to be deafened, blinded or over stimulated in general.  Simply put, if you have an IC reason to look - then look and feel free to put your finger to your eye and look around, even if no one is there to watch you do it.  That helps me stay in character.<br>
<br>
~D <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theherald@scbnforum58570>The Herald</A> at: 2/18/03 11:32:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stephencrowley>Stephen Crowley</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/18/03 11:59:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lagoon.freebsd.lublin.pl/~fenix/smieci/graf/rozne/vampire/camarilla.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rules Clarication - Obfuscate</span><hr size=1> In character reason to look... like say the Seneschal is debriefing the Prince on the prior week's activities, and a certain neonate Nos, in an act of pure silliness, actually eavesdrops in ob, fighting off the Seneschal's efforts to detect him with Auspex? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Excellent example, Darren. Thank you, both of you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=antoineleblanc@scbnforum58570>Antoine leblanc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/19/03 12:35:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Clarification - Obfuscate</span><hr size=1> While i'm not aware of and specific dicipline level that allow you to avoid cameras, there is 3 point merit in the Nosferatu ClanBook, which allows Mask to be recorded.  However, the table top book does suggest that looking at a security monitor in real time is not proof against obfuscate. <br>
